The Chronicle Chronicle Reporters Zimbabweans have largely observed Government’s call to stay at home and limit movement as a measure to contain the spread of Covid-19. The usually busy and noisy Bulawayo-Harare Road section that passes through the Bulawayo CBD is conspicuous by its silence and lack of activity. <img class="alignnone wp-image-493596 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-27-680x453.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="453" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-27.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-27-360x240.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The usual sound of pirating Harare buses and touts sounding horns to lure customers is absent. It’s very quiet and only a handful of cars have moved on the road since 6AM. <img class="alignnone wp-image-493593 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-24-680x453.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="453" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-24.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-24-360x240.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Only a few people are queuing at major retail shops in the central business district to buy essentials goods. <img class="alignnone wp-image-493591 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-23-680x453.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="453" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-23.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-23-360x240.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Most shops selling nonessential goods are closed. <img class="alignnone wp-image-493583 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-20-680x453.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="453" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-20.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-20-360x240.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The lockdown is however affected by water cuts as the Bulawayo City Council has been struggling to restore supplies in some of the suburbs since Saturday, March 21. <img class="alignnone wp-image-493561 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-9-680x510.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="510" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-9.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-9-360x270.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Pumula South has not received tap water since council embarked on a citywide water shutdown while council has not delivered a water bowser. <img class="alignnone wp-image-493546 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-1-680x510.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="510" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-1.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-1-360x270.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Residents are forced to fetch water from boreholes, resulting in some of them not observing social distancing. <img class="alignnone wp-image-493548 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-2-680x510.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="510" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-2.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-2-360x270.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> A few people who defied the order and some who had found their way into the city centre to buy basic commodities were peacefully Shepherded back home by the police. <img class="alignnone wp-image-493565 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-11-680x453.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="453" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-11.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-11-360x240.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Gweru residents are complying with the Government directive to exercise extreme caution by isolating themselves and staying at home. <img class="alignnone wp-image-493581 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-18-680x453.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="453" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-18.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-18-360x240.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> In Mkoba suburbs all shops are closed except for Choppies which was open from 7am-11am. <img class="alignnone wp-image-493563 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-10-680x453.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="453" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-10.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-10-360x240.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Shops which were found open were asked to close by the police. <img class="alignnone wp-image-493595 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-26-680x453.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="453" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-26.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-26-360x240.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />  Midlands Minister of State Larry Mavhima implored people to continue complying with the directive for their safety and that of their families. <img class="alignnone wp-image-493579 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-17-680x453.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="453" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-17.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-17-360x240.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Business operators in Victoria Falls are on lockdown. The central business district resembles a ghost town with no shops open and only occasional human movement. Big supermarkets are open but there are no queues. Total and Puma fuel services stations have long winding queues as motorists wait for fuel which has not been delivered. <img class="alignnone wp-image-493551 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-4-680x510.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="510" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-4.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-4-360x270.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> While the Victoria Falls border post remains open for cargo, the Rainforest and curio markets are closed. The situation is a bit different in the high-density suburbs where people are going ahead with their normal activities. <img class="alignnone wp-image-493557 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-7-680x385.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="385" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-7.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-7-360x204.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />  All businesses including tuckshops are open and children are playing on the streets. <img class="alignnone wp-image-493560 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-8-680x510.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="510" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-8.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-8-360x270.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Some pirate taxis were operating since morning but police are also on the ground checking on vehicles and ordering those carrying more than two people to make a u-turn. <img class="alignnone wp-image-493549 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-3-680x510.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="510" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-3.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/lockdown-3-360x270.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Vegetable markets remain open and vendors say they will not close because they are maintaining the one-metre apart social distancing rule. In Hwange, big supermarkets are open while public transport has stopped operating. Most travellers and residents of Beitbridge have started complying with the national response plan to minimise the spread of the Covid-19
pandemic. <img class="alignnone wp-image-493598 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/Untitled-2-12-680x380-680x380.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/Untitled-2-12-680x380.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/Untitled-2-12-680x380-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> When our news crew visited the usually busy business centres and markets, most traders had scaled down operations while others closed
shop yesterday. At Mashavire, Mashakada, Engen, Ha Mbedzi and Ha Mangavha there were no people at the market stalls, bars were closed and only grocery shops were open with few clients. Further, the police are on patrol in the border town. <img class="alignnone wp-image-493599 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/Untitled-3-8-680x510.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="510" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/Untitled-3-8.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/Untitled-3-8-360x270.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> At Dulivhadzimu bus terminus, business was literally dead after many people traveled to their rural homes between Friday and Sunday.
There was also limited movement of people through the border except for cargo traffic and customs clearing agents who are facilitating
regional and international trade. <img class="alignnone wp-image-493601 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/Untitled-4-4-680x510.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="510" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/Untitled-4-4.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/Untitled-4-4-360x270.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The Assistant Regional Immigration Officer in charge of Beitbridge (Zimbabwe), Mr Nqobile Ncube said they was limited traffic and that
very few people had tried to cross into either country. “We are working together with other security agents and our security guards who are strategically positioned to screen traffic and enforce
compliance,” he said. <img class="alignnone wp-image-493604 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/Untitled-6-3-680x510.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="510" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/Untitled-6-3.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2020/03/Untitled-6-3-360x270.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> “There is not much traffic that is coming through. You will note that on Sunday we cleared a total of 351 truck drivers on the arrival
section and 234 on exits. “It is pleasing to note that word has got to everyone and people are observing a high level of compliance with the ongoing measures to
contain this condition.”